Description: Inter-Family Office Synergy
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: PACTUM PARTNERS was founded on the understanding that sophisticated family offices, aligned through shared missions, visions, and values, would benefit from a partner dedicated to fostering co-investment and peer collaboration. Family Offices, in ever increasing numbers, leverage their entrepreneurial DNA in the pursuit of direct investments. Offices struggle to review proposed investments due to a lack of trust, experience, staff, and/or time. The challenges, associated with the rise in direct investments, encourage a desire for co- investment with like-minded entities. A misalignment in values and horizons, alongside an environment of high fees, drives family offices from traditional investments in public equities and fund structures. High standards with regards to privacy, discretion, and security further limit potential strategic partners. We believe that the best long-term partner for family offices are other family offices. Uniquely capable of leveraging their significant shared expertise, capital, and influence, inter-family office partnerships provide an attractive alternative to traditional fund managers by operating with greater control and flexibility without facing limiting time horizons, high fees, and regulatory restrictions. The opportunity for cross-collaboration often presents itself beyond the traditional realm of capital allocation.

They have worked in all industries and through all stages of companies - from startup through multi-billion in revenues - but their “sweet spot” over the past 10 years has been in the Technology and Manufacturing/Industrial/Business Services sectors. In the Tech industry, the majority of their clients have been venture capital or private equity backed, and have been startup through IPO/$100M’s in revenues. On the Industrial side, again, all have been primarily VC or PE backed enterprises. Their scope is international and they have successfully completed retained executive search assignments in all theaters worldwide. The Firm is led by Partners who actually “do the work” versus the industry which typically employs a Partner and Associate “split the work” model. Their clients tell us that the Partner executed model works best since all of their business is repeat and/or word of mouth. Unlike the Industry, they have no members of their firm who are business development focused resources. The Firm is led by their 3 Managing Partners: Stephen Sterett, Paul Bailey, and Logan Moodley. They have 60 plus years of retained executive search experience combined between them, and were recruited to the Firm by their Founder. In 2002, Chip retired from the firm and search industry and Paul and Stephen took over the Firm.

In this program Salesconx recruits a team of independent commission only sales agents who work to deliver qualified introductions and deals for your business. After 90 days you will have an up and running sales team complete with pipeline. You then have the option to either a.) keep going with the virtual sales team through Salesconx or b.) retain (FT or Independent) those sales team members that are actually performing. ** Salesconx Masters. Our skilled blacksmiths -sometimes second or third generation employees- make every item from start to finish using age-old forging methods. 30 years ago Stone County Ironworks began to reinvigorate the lost art of blacksmithing. Every hand-tool and essential piece of equipment used by the Village Smithy in the 1800’s is still integral to the way we make things today. You won’t find two Stone County pieces that are identical.
